import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['x'])
    plt.xlabel('X-coordinates')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the x-coordinates of the points?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
from scipy.spatial.distance import pdist, squareform

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    # Calculate pairwise distances between points
    distances = pdist(data)
    
    # Calculate the average distance
    avg_distance = np.mean(distances)
    
    # Create a heatmap of point density
    heatmap, xedges, yedges = np.histogram2d(data['x'], data['y'], bins=50)
    extent = [xedges[0], xedges[-1], yedges[0], yedges[-1]]
    
    plt.imshow(heatmap.T, extent=extent, origin='lower', cmap='hot')
    plt.colorbar(label='Point Density')
    
    # Add a line for the average distance
    plt.axhline(avg_distance, color='blue', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    plt.title("What is the average distance between the points?")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
